The main thing you need to know about level 0 is SSH login
SSH stands for Secure SHell (also known as Secure Socket Shell)
It is an internet protocol thet sets up a client server connection, and it uses asymmetric cryptography to encrypt data.

 SSH sets up a connection between a user's device and a faraway machine, often a server. 
Here you will be connecting to the OTW's bandit lab, which provides you a playground with restricted permissions to try the tasks provided

